Chinese users. We accomplish this by analyzing profile images on two social networking
sites, Facebook in the US and Renren in China. Our findings indicate that self-presentation
is sensitive to national culture: Chinese users are more likely to customize their
profile images than Americans. Our study suggests that there is a need to design social
