the data. Most of the literature on time-series data visualization either focus on
a small number of tasks or a specific domain. We propose KronoMiner, a tool that embeds
new interaction and visualization techniques as well as analytical capabilities for
the visual exploration of time-series data. The interface's design has been iteratively
refined based on feedback from expert users. Qualitative evaluation with an expert
user not involved in the design process indicates that our prototype is promising
for further research.},
booktitle = {Proceedings of the SIGCHI Conference on Human Factors in Computing Systems},
pages = {1737–1746},
numpages = {10},
