photos using the metaphor of passing paper photos around. The prototype encourages
people to share their devices and use them interchangeably while discussing photos
face-to-face. The prototype supports ad-hoc photo sharing in different contexts by
taking into account the spatial arrangement of users around a table, measured with
sensors embedded in their mobile phones. Our evaluations show that people are willing
to share and connect their mobile phones to engage in collaborative interactions.
Participants were able to easily share their collections of photos using our proposed
interaction techniques.},
