guideline for creating effective animated transitions has long been the use of slow-in/slow-out
pacing, but no empirical data exist to support this practice. We remedy this by studying
object tracking performance under different conditions of temporal distortion, i.e.,
constant speed transitions, slow-in/slow-out, fast-in/fast-out, and an adaptive technique
that slows down the visually complex parts of the animation. Slow-in/slow-out outperformed
other techniques, but we saw technique differences depending on the type of visual
transition.},
