make selections by twisting the ring and "click" by sliding it along the finger. The
ring - the size of a regular wedding band - is magnetic, and is tracked by a wrist-worn
sensor. Nenya's tiny size, eyes-free usability, and physical form indistinguishable
from a regular ring make its use subtle and socially acceptable. We present two user
studies (one- and two-handed) in which we studied sighted and eyes-free use, finding
that even with no visual feedback users were able to select from eight targets.},
