usage scenario of a native-language CAPTCHA mechanism was conducted in order to investigate
several aspects that affect end-user perceptions related to the quality of CAPTCHA.
A total of 210 participants of age between 19 and 64 participated during May and July
2010. The survey results validate the common belief that CAPTCHAs are still difficult
for humans to solve. They also provide insights that can be applied to improve users'
experience on interacting with CAPTCHA systems.},
booktitle = {Proceedings of the SIGCHI Conference on Human Factors in Computing Systems},
