digital game of cat and mouse that allows cats to participate in play through a species-appropriate
interface. The game applies Human-Computer Interaction (HCI) principles to pets and
casts pets as participants in the gaming experience. During the pilot study, pet owners
characterized CCR as a mutually positive experience, describing the game as a fun
way to play. CCR explores the effects of including pets in the digital gaming experience.},
booktitle = {Proceedings of the SIGCHI Conference on Human Factors in Computing Systems},
