disruptions, were not rare, especially in large distributed projects. Overall, one-third
of all projects experienced at least one member relocating but most moves reflected
churn across high-ranking institutions. When collaborators moved, the project was
disrupted. Our data suggest that moves exemplify normal disruptions. A design challenge
is to help projects adapt to disruption.},
