a detailed evaluation in which therapists independent of the design team used the
game with 6 adolescents experiencing clinical anxiety disorders; a study in which
a member of the design team used the game with 15 adolescents; and finally a study
assessing the acceptability of the game and intervention with 216 practicing therapists.
Findings are presented within the context of a framework for the design and evaluation
of complex health interventions. The paper provides an in-depth insight into the use
of therapeutic games to support adolescent interventions and provides stronger evidence
