describe our actuation concepts, prototypes, and measurements showing that magnetic
fields can change physical effects in a linear way. Controlled experiments reveal
that participants can tactually distinguish four rendered resistance levels of a button
prototype and easily detect dynamic detents in a continuous slider. Finally, we describe
