comments on a news website, the time taken to write them, and the number of issue-relevant
thoughts they contain, we demonstrate that participants conform to high vs. low norms
of thoughtfulness manifested through either the apparent behavior of other users or
through visual, textual and interactional design features conceptually associated
with thoughtfulness. Theoretical and applied insights for designing online participatory
environments are discussed.},
